column5: For the past few months I've been, albeit slowly, developing an new website.  The ultimate objective is to make it the Unofficial Ontario Fishing Encyclopedia, ie everything you could want to know about fishing techniques and information for this great province of ours.   I've got enough content now so theres stuff to look at, the dirctory is working and as time goes on and I get more information, I'm going to keep adding it to the site, future segments will include lake information and more categories of fish etc.  But i gotta LAUNCH it sometime, so here goes!!!  When you get a chance, please check out  (insert drum roll here...)  Please  let me introduce.........  www.ontarioangler.com    www.ontarioangler.com

ha ha ha!  TJ, that came up in one of my frequent searches yesterday!  I just now clicked on it and sure enough all the links I hit on it then are colored.  At the time I thought it was another section of OFC I hadn't yet visited. So, when do you sleep...?  Seems to me you're needing the 24 hours a day working on all these sites?  Michael

LOL.. im a collector of great domain names.. lol.. its an accumulation of 10 years of content, ill have videos and a lake section, all the cartoons ive ever bought... more stuff on the way...  Suggestions as to other content would be good too!  (also advertisers wanted .. wink wink..)  Im about to get the muskie section done, some carp info as well.

(rapidly counts change in pockets & on dresser) How much advertising can I get for $11.62?  Oh, wait, need to hold a couple quarters for shopping carts, make that $11.12. Seriously, just in case I ever do have an advertising budget, where can I find out about it? Thanks! Michael

Interesting.  I too ran across this web site a few days ago.  I thought - man does the format look awfully familiar.   I'll be sure to check it out.  TJ - You gonna tie all this together from a central point some day.
Looks good T.J.  As a newbie to fishing I can see I'll be spending some quality time on this new site.

Thanks guys, lol.. when someone buys out the massive network, lol.. ill tell 'em where all the sites are. I am glad its hitting the search engines well already!!  When I had an opportunity to get the domain name failry cheap, I couldn't resist, it took me a year to figure out what I wanted to do with it.
Well done T.J.    There is a ton of info in there
Looks good Boss! Loads of good reading in there!
where are the lake trout pics?!
LOL. there coming.. I need 30 hours in a day to get everything done..  also ive got muskie content to add!
Great website. Already learned a thing or two from some of the articles.  Good stuff.
I like,I like. gives me something to read when im bored. helpful too.
